Results\: Download From - List of file(s) to download in non-absolute path format Full Path to Use - Full path where downloaded files will be placed Exit Code - Exit code of the step needed for branching. 047aa454-1259-49e1-ad64-e28da221eab6.c85b41eb-fc87-4c7d-bba9-5a78945be59b.description=c30668a1-79a2-463a-af9d-ac80ce860d6f.bcca94c1-0651-441c-925f-cc6787315c90.description 047aa454-1259-49e1-ad64-e28da221eab6.description=
 Purpose

Install and/or configure Oracle supplied ASMLib.

 Description

Installation and/or configuration of the Oracle supplied ASMLib.
Install specified rpms.
Check that the required libraries are installed.
Create the labels for the specified disks.
Workflow required one of (or both) the parameters "ASMLib RPMs" or "ASM Disk List".

 Required Inputs

    Server Target - The desired target to run this flow against.
    Server Target Username - The user to login to the Server Target as.
    Server Target Password - The password to login as the Server Target Username.
    Download Source Host - The target host where the files needed for this flow can be downloaded from.
    Download Source Path - The path to where the files can be found on the Download Source Host.
    ASM Disk List - *Required if configuring ASM disks. Left blank if no ASM disks are being configured.  Comma separated list of ASM Labels and unformated devices partitions. Example\: VOL1\:/dev/sdc1,VOL2\:/dev/sdc2,VOL3\:/dev/sdd1
    ASM Software Group - *Required\: The primary group of the ASM software directory (ORACLE_HOME)
    ASM Software Owner - *Required\: The primary owner of the ASM software directory (ORACLE_HOME)
    ASMLib RPMs - *Required if installing oracleasm rpms.  Leave blank if only configuring ASM disks. Comma separated list of oracleasm rpms to install.
    Oracle Account - *Required\: The user who owns ORACLE_HOME. Left blank for Windows.
    Server.Become Routine - No description
    Target Directory - *Required if downloading files to the target system.  The directory on the target machine where the files will be downloaded.

 Optional Inputs

    Clean Code Base - Remove code base from target after execution (True || False).
    Clean JRE - Remove JRE from target after execution (True || False).
    Download From SA - Download binaries from SA (True || False). Must set override for 'SAUser' System Account.
    SA Folder Path - Location of binaries on SA. Must set override for 'SAUser' System Account.
    Debug Level - Set level of output [(least) 1-5 (most)]
    Cluster Nodes - *Optional\: Comma separated list of RAC nodes.

 Additional Documentation

Additional information, including the _HP Database and Middleware Automation Support Matrix_ and solution pack user guides, are available via HP Live Network\:

"http\://hpln.hp.com/group/database-and-middleware-automation"\:http\://hpln.hp.com/group/database-and-middleware-automation

To access the documentation, click the RESOURCES link and enter your HP Passport credentials.
